From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: CI <ci@example.com>
Date: Sat, 8 Mar 2026 09:35:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] fix: add missing cstdint include for uint32_t

The ge_error_codes.h uses uint32_t but doesn't include the required header.
This causes compilation errors with newer GCC versions.

---
 third_party/acl/inc/ge/ge_error_codes.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/third_party/acl/inc/ge/ge_error_codes.h b/third_party/acl/inc/ge/ge_error_codes.h
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/third_party/acl/inc/ge/ge_error_codes.h
+++ b/third_party/acl/inc/ge/ge_error_codes.h
@@ -15,6 +15,7 @@
 #endif
 #endif

+#include <stdint.h>
 #include <stddef.h>

 #ifdef __cplusplus
--
2.43.0
